StoryAsset.name: Short Post Match Cup Leg 1 of 1 Semifinal

keyValuePair.Value: Into the Final! How did you pull it off?
You must be happy and excited, knowing you're through to the Final after this victory. It was comfortable in the end, too. How would you sum up your team's performance?
Our attacking quality made the difference.

I'm delighted for the whole team. We're always confident that we have the attacking quality to win games. We can always make chances. We've always got goals in us. Now it's about making sure our standards don't drop. No point going to a Final if you don't lift the silverware!
We looked very assured.

It looked like an easy win, a two-goal margin. But I think credit for that goes to all the hard work the boys did when we didn't have the ball. We looked solid defensively and that freed the rest of the team to go out and play. Now we need to make sure we're as well-organised as that in the Final!

It looked like an easy win, a two-goal margin. But I think credit for that goes to all the hard work the boys did when we didn't have the ball. We looked solid defensively and that freed the rest of the team to go out and play. Now we need to make sure we're as well-organised as that in the Final!
It's all about the Final now!
I was surprised, really, that we won so comfortably. I'm happy, of course. But we need to be focused now. The Final will be a different kind of challenge altogether.
IT was close but you did it! What made the difference?
Semi-finals are always tight games with such a big prize at stake. But your boys kept their nerve and squeezed through to the Final. What made the difference today?
Semi-finals are always tight games with such a big prize at stake. But your boys kept their nerve and squeezed through to the Final. What made the difference today?
We have to build on this.

It was close but I thought we deserved to win. The boys were great. And now we're through to the Final against %1s. We will need to play as well as we did in this game to be in with a chance of lifting the trophy, that's for sure.
The hard work was worth it.

I watched the players in training this week and I could see how motivated they were for this game. They've left everything out on that pitch. But we've achieved nothing yet. I want us to go into the Final ready to go to work all over again.
Cool heads and a good plan!

We had a plan to deal with our opponents and we had the nerve to see it through, even though the scoreline was pretty close in the end. I've always known the benefit of having experienced players in our line-up. And now they've taken us into the Final.
The fans were chanting Easy! Easy! Was it?
That was an absolute demolition job and you've stormed through to the Final. The fans were chanting Easy! Easy! but I'm sure it wasn't as simple as that. What made the difference for your boys today?
It was about good preparation.

You don't win a %1s semi-final by that sort of margin thanks to a couple of good individual performances. The lads looked fit and prepared. Players put their bodies on the line when they had to. Hard work and good preparation, it's was as simple as that.
It was a real team performance.

I thought we dominated all over the pitch. We snuffed out all %1s's best attacking moments and then looked really dangerous going forward. I hope the lads work hard in training and make sure they've got some goals left in them for the Final!

I thought we dominated all over the pitch. We snuffed out all %1s's best attacking moments and then looked really dangerous going forward. I hope the lads work hard in training and make sure they've got some goals left in them for the Final!
That's a great achievement.

To win a %1s semi-final and by a three-goal margin is something that doesn't happen very often. Every single player deserves enormous credit. But we can't take too long thinking about it. We've got a Final to prepare for now!
A narrow defeat. What could you have done differently?
It's disappointing to lose by such as narrow margin at this stage of a big competition. Do you have any regrets? Could you have approached the game differently?
This isn't the time for analysing the game.

I thought the boys played well. Today %1s were probably just the better team. In due course, we'll look back and analyse things, see what we could have done better. We'll learn from this experience, that's for sure.
We gave it our best shot.

Of course we're disappointed but we didn't play badly. I think the fans will recognise that we had heroes all over the pitch. We've got this far and come up short. We'll just have to improve and come back stronger.
I expect us to improve.

We couldn't always cope with their movement and the cleverness of some of their attacking play. Our boys worked hard out there but they know they have to be better in possession. We'll look back at the game and see where we can improve.
Do you have to make a fresh start now?

After such a heavy defeat, you must be aware of how far you need to go to be able to compete against the best. Is this a time when you start looking at your squad and wondering if you need to bring in better players?
It's about gaining experience.
It's about gaining experience.

It was a semi-final and it was the first time this group has had to deal with the pressure that comes with such a big game. I respect what they've done to get us this far. It's not about making changes now. It's about learning from the experience.

It was a semi-final and it was the first time this group has had to deal with the pressure that comes with such a big game. I respect what they've done to get us this far. It's not about making changes now. It's about learning from the experience.
I have to work out a way forward now.

To be really honest about it, we were just second-best in all areas today. We took a bit of a hiding out there. We got this far but we we've been well beaten. Do we need to change our tactics or change our team? That's what I need to decide now.
We'll take time over our decisions.

Look, we were well beaten. We couldn't cope with the quality of their attacking play. Lots of our boys will know they have to be better than they were today. Let's deal with the disappointment of missing out on the Final and then make careful decisions about where we go from here.
